data.title: How to Migrate the Computer objects from Source to Target Domain were users already created in Target Domain
data.text:
The workstation is a member of the source domain and the user that uses the workstation is a member of the target domain. I will assume a one-way trust as that is required to allows target users to login to source joined workstations.

The migration process is the same as all other migrations. The only difference in your case is there is NOTHING to update for the target user on the workstation as any permissions they have are already tied to their target account.

Deploy agent (discovery task)

Resource process task

Move task to join yo the target

Clean up task to remove the agent.

all product documentation can be found here. https://support.quest.com/migration-manager-for-ad/8.15/technical-documents

This section of this document outline a lot in this area, but there is. No single step by step for just the process. The overall topic is larger and documented as such.

HI Jeff,

Thanks for your response.

I think the statement your provided that will work for On-premises Workstations.
